I was hesitant to spend $5, but comparing it elsewhere (i.e. $20 for the Nintendo 3DS version), I decided it was a steal! I easily spent 20 hours on this game, doing the challenges, getting the characters, and getting the extras. It was well worth what I paid.  All of your favorite characters are in this game - X Men, Fantastic 4, Spider-Man, the Avengers, and others. There are also multiple versions of the same character, which is fun. All characters have their own unique super moves that introduce an element of strategy to completing the challenges in each level. Characters have different play-styles too - Wolverine is fast so it makes sense for him to be a brawler, whereas Black Widow has a good ranged attacked so it is better to sit back.  Most of it was a little on the easy side, but there are a few challenges that will definitely test your skill (i.e. getting the Spider-Man Symbiote suit is a BEAST).  The controls are a little frustrating at times - the two finger swipe up to fly isn't 100% effective, and sometimes when you character needs to charge an object with lightning, it auto selects the wrong target. Notwithstanding, this game was an absolute blast.
